			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>Happy Coincidence regarding the TAUNT skill?</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#000000" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I don't know if this has ever been thoroughly tested, and perhaps I shouldn't even bother propagating what could potentially become a rumor, but I am curious what other more experienced SKs have discovered regarding success rates when using the TAUNT skill.<br />
<br />
It could be complete coincidence, but the other day while exping in the Tower of Sol Ro I was having some trouble performing a successful TAUNT on the Soldiers there when breaking a mezz.  This wasn't a big problem, however, because I was able to obtain aggro by simply casting CD on them a few times (they are immune to the spell but the aggro is still generated, and it casting it on them didn't break the mezz).  I did discover something curious that I want to explore further.<br />
<br />
I found that if I sat down next to the mezzed mob first, THEN used my taunt skill, I seemed to have a 100% success rate.<br />
<br />
Is it possible that since I was next to them sitting, my proximity aggro jumped me so high up on their aggro list that landing a successful taunt was easier?<br />
<br />
Was I just lucky?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
